parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause electrical fires, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ignition switch is hard to turn
the dash lights do not come on
the vehicle stalls or shuts down without warning
the ignition switch melts or overheats
and the vehicle's engine hesitates or backfires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at high speeds. It can also lead to a loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or quits without warning
and the vehicle's engine skips or runs rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at high speeds. It can also lead to electrical fires, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the dash lights do not come on
the vehicle's engine hesitates or backfires
the ignition switch melts or overheats
and the vehicle's wiring harness gets too hot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of engine mounts can cause the engine to move excessively, leading to premature wear on other components, noise, and vibration, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potential fires, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: and temperature gauge in the red zone.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lunge forward, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
Subframe and steering failure can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The corrosion and failure of the subframe can cause loss of steering, accidents, and damage to other vehicle components.
symptoms: The subframe detaches from the body mount
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the engine cradle support bushings corrode
the rear subframe drops onto the steering column
the upper retainer bolt on the rear subframe breaks
the lower subframe nut plate and body mounts break due to corrosion.

preventing occupants from exiting the vehicle.
